description.en: The work of a vehicle from the time it leaves a Parking Point after parking until its next return to park at a Parking Point.
Time when the Block ended.

usage.en: in principle this can be derived from the start time of the last Vehicle Journey and the finishing duration.

description.en: The Parking Point where the Block ended at.

usage.en: A vehicle's return to park at a Parking Point marks the end of a Block.

description.en: Time when the Block started.

usage.en: In principle this can be derived from the start time of the first Vehicle Journey and the preparation duration.

description.en: The Parking Point where the Block started at.
Vehicle Type used to execute the Block.
The DayType when the Block was worked on.

usage.en: For example: weekday in school holidays.

A VehicleJourney is the defined movement of a vehicle using a specified Journey Pattern on a particular Route. By virtue of being defined for a Day Type, a Vehicle Journey is a class of journeys that would take place at the same time on each day of a specified Day Type.
